page.title: 11ECOLOGY PLANT SURVEY
page.content: W.I.Denton survey. The conservation field map ref.86,33 on the East side of the road was at first planted with conifers which died.It has since been planted with deciduous trees by Welby Estate.There is a pond in the field with water fowl.40plants and 7 trees & shrubs were found. Hogweed, Birds eye trefoil, Cinqfoil, Thistle - welted, Lesser yellow trefoil, Yarrow, Common vetch, Broad leaf dock, Birds Eye speedwell, Marestail, Blackberry, Narrow leaf plantain, Goosegrass, Knapweed, Dandelion, Common dock, Hedgewoundwort, Bindweed, Creeping thistle, Willow herb, Dog rose, 2 Sallow willows, Elder, Common nettle, Green field speedwell, Marsh birds foot trefoil, Ivy, Chickweed - mouse eared, Red clover,
